<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-24T11:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-24T11:14:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/332.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-24T11:00:00-05:14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>American Consul General at Guayaquil informs me that he has not heard
                            from American Consular Agent at Esmeraldas for several weeks.
                            Revolutionists still control Esmeraldas. Conditions politically have
                            been less serious for the last two weeks, but many persons here
                            anticipate an attack on the Government forces here on January 28, the
                            anniversary of the assassination of former President Alfaro.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
